text: Knoben R, van der Wal B (2020). Dutch Foundation for Applied Water Research (STOWA) - Limnodata Neerlandica. Dutch Foundation for Applied Water Research. Occurrence dataset https://doi.org/10.15468/ennulm accessed via GBIF.org on 2023-05-17.
access: 26 water boards, the provinces and the Ministry of Transport, Public Works and Water Management. Over 20,000 sample points were used. The main purpose of the dataset is monitoring the quality of Dutch surface waters. Next to the biological characteristics also a-biotic data were sampled and stored alongside the biotic data. Observations are available from phytoplankton, diatoms, aquatic and riparian plants, macro-invertebrates and fish. The data were collected on a yearly base. The taxonomy has been validated according to the Dutch standardised checklist of aquatic species."
